During our hike we made a great discovery of the arboretum, access to which is free. How lucky to be able to enjoy this large, remarkable garden surrounded by splendid trees that we appreciated as being ideal for meditation. We were surprised by the diversity of their origins. A relaxing green setting for a breath of fresh air in the heart of Paris.

Just opposite the magnificent gardens of the Breuil school, you can complete the walk by strolling through the paths of the Paris arboretum. It‚Äôs nice because some parts of the route are in the shade. Allow around half an hour to go around it. Everything is accessible by stroller with small wheels üòâ

Easy to access by public transport, by RER A, station: Joinville-Le-Pont (less than 10mm). Beautiful green space with many varieties of trees, some are magnificent (also, at the very beginning of spring, some trees are already starting to flower, a delight for the eyes); what's more, very peaceful/calm. A good moment of enrichment and relaxation, especially for lovers of nature and tranquility/calm.
Beautiful, fairly wild, shaded park with some very beautiful trees. It's quite spartan but pleasant except that unfortunately you can hear the surrounding car traffic.
A true haven of peace, the garden of the Breuil school is splendid. ‚ù§Ô∏è One of the most beautiful floral parks in the capital. I will definitely come back. ‚úåÔ∏è
Super nice place, quite quiet. It allows you to walk, rest and learn about the different species of trees.
Gorgeous ! An enchanted place at the gates of Paris
Small park located next to the Bois de Vincennes which can be visited in 30 minutes, perfect for children. There are a lot of runners in the park, it's a shame to share narrow paths with them

It‚Äôs a very nice place. I visited it in spring to see the diversity of trees as well as in winter to run. Generally there aren't many people so it's not bad for running or matching between the trees and the lakes.

I have lived near the Bois de Vincennes for several years and I had never heard of the Paris Arboretum or even the garden of the Breuil school which is just opposite... If you like flora, go take a look, it's really interesting, even in winter! :D
Open and very friendly place with different species of trees whose names are mostly indicated on small labels. To have. Thank you for this pleasant space.
A little paradise. Incredible tree species

An educational place to learn about ornamental and vegetable plants as well as garden design on one side: rest, pond... On the other a collection of trees: maples, oaks, willows..., small streams and freshness in the appointment.

The Paris Arborium is truly an amazing place. You discover many species of trees in a calm environment. There are very few people who know them. In addition you are opposite the Breuil school, which is the Paris gardening school, garden location is spectacular.
A beautiful and quiet botanical garden. There are few people. The park is well maintained. Great for walking, photography.
Superb collection of magnificent trees with different species if you are looking to connect with nature it's here

A green space with common and original tree species. Magnificent when flowering in spring. Passing by the lilacs in bloom it is impossible not to stop to enjoy the scent and sight of these delicate and abundant flowers, and to resist the urge to take such a beautiful branch with you... but hey, so that all visitors or passers-by can enjoy it at their leisure, we must give up this selfish pleasure, even if it means staying a little longer to savor the moment more üòä

A beautiful walk in spring, this place is very calm and the different varieties of trees are very well documented, also opposite the arboretum there is the magnificent botanical garden of the Breuil school, also to visit by the same occasion !

A pleasant place of relaxation to spend time alone or with family. The small water courts are endless sources of games and stories for children. A little corner of paradise just a stone's throw from the RER A. For flora enthusiasts, this is an ideal place because there are a multitude of trees and plants of different species.
A natural setting not far from Paris, a super pleasant walk!
Very pleasant to visit; very nice place, peaceful and interesting

If you like trees and plants this place is for you. A magnificent garden maintained by the students of the Breuil school. After a horse race at the Vincennes racecourse which is just a stone's throw away, nothing better than getting some fresh air and relaxing in the arboretum.
Beautiful collection of many different trees.
Place with a lot of charm, I have the impression that it is not very well known and therefore attendance is reasonable. I came across a red squirrel!
The trees are all different and we can clearly see that in this place.
Quiet and relaxing place where classes of all ages, hikers, walkers and runners meet.
